---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Books for Sports Parents"
  description="The books we actually recommend for parents who coach, drive, and live the youth sports schedule. Sports psychology, parenting, talent development, and coaching fundamentals."
>
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-3 font-medium">Reading list</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-ink text-[2.5rem] md:text-[4rem] leading-[1.0] font-medium">
        Books worth reading <em class="text-rust">before the season starts</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-xl md:text-2xl mt-6 max-w-2xl leading-snug">
        Thirteen books. Four categories. All links go to our <a href="https://bookshop.org/shop/ParentCoachDesk" class="text-rust hover:underline" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Bookshop.org store</a>, which supports independent bookstores.
      </p>
      <p class="font-display italic text-ink-soft text-sm mt-3 max-w-2xl">
        Partner links — we earn a small commission when you buy. We only list books we've read and recommend.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Sports Parenting */}
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-2 font-medium">Sports parenting</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.05] font-medium mb-8">
        For the parent on the <em class="text-rust">sideline</em>.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Changing the Game</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">John O'Sullivan</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            The clearest book on why youth sports go sideways and what parents can do about it. Covers the cost-benefit of travel, the problem with early pressure, and what a good season actually looks like. Read it in August before the season starts.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-changing-the-game/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Whose Game Is It, Anyway?</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Richard Ginsburg, Stephen Durant, Amy Baltzell</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Three Harvard sports psychologists writing for parents. Age-by-age framework for what kids actually need from the adults in their sports life at each stage of development.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-whose-game-is-it-anyway/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Beyond Winning</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Kim John Payne</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Short games, long childhoods. Makes the case for backing off — and explains what gets lost when the adult agenda runs the schedule. Good read for any parent who wonders if they're doing too much.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-beyond-winning/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Positive Coaching</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Jim Thompson</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Practical, not preachy. The Positive Coaching Alliance founder covers what actually builds character and self-esteem through sport — and what just looks like it does.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-positive-coaching/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Mental Performance */}
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-2 font-medium">Mental performance</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.05] font-medium mb-8">
        For the conversation on the <em class="text-rust">drive home</em>.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Mindset</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Carol Dweck</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Fixed versus growth. The distinction changes how you talk to your kid after a bad game, a missed shot, or a cut from a team. Short book. Worth reading before tryout season every year.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-mindset/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Grit</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Angela Duckworth</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            What separates kids who improve from kids who plateau has less to do with natural talent than most parents assume. Good read for mid-season when your kid wants to quit something they started.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-grit/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Mind Gym</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Gary Mack</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Written for athletes but short enough that parents read it too. Chapters run two to three pages. Pass it to your kid at thirteen and read it alongside them.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-mind-gym/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">The Champion's Mind</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Jim Afremow</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            More practical than most sports psychology books. Written by a working sports psychologist. Covers confidence, focus, and performance pressure in plain language.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-champions-mind/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Talent Development */}
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-2 font-medium">Talent development</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.05] font-medium mb-8">
        For the parent who wants to understand <em class="text-rust">how kids get good</em>.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">The Talent Code</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Daniel Coyle</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            The best book on how skill actually develops. Covers myelin, deep practice, and coaching. Changes how you watch practice and what you notice your kid doing right.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-talent-code/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Range</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">David Epstein</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            The case for multi-sport kids. Most elite athletes were generalists longer than you'd expect. Direct counter to early specialization pressure, backed by research across dozens of fields.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-range/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">Peak</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Anders Ericsson</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            The science behind deliberate practice, from the researcher who coined the term. More useful for coaches and serious parent-coaches than for casual reading. Best paired with The Talent Code.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-peak/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Coaching */}
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-2 font-medium">Coaching</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.05] font-medium mb-8">
        For the parent running <em class="text-rust">the practice</em>.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">The Inner Game of Tennis</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">W. Timothy Gallwey</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            Old but still the best book on not coaching too much. Applies to every sport. The core argument: the interference between knowing something and doing it is the whole problem, and most coaching makes it worse.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-inner-game-of-tennis/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-bone bg-paper p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-medium leading-tight">The Little Book of Talent</h3>
          <p class="font-display italic text-rust text-sm mt-1 font-medium">Daniel Coyle</p>
          <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base mt-3 leading-snug">
            52 short tips drawn from The Talent Code. Each one runs a page or two. Practical for a parent running a practice or helping a kid train at home. Keep it in the car.
          </p>
          <a href="/go/book-little-book-of-talent/" class="inline-block mt-4 font-display text-sm text-rust hover:underline font-medium" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Buy on Bookshop.org ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Store link */}
  <section>
    <div class="container-px py-12">
      <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-base max-w-xl leading-snug">
        All books link to our <a href="https://bookshop.org/shop/ParentCoachDesk" class="text-rust hover:underline" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener">Bookshop.org storefront</a>. Every purchase supports independent bookstores. We earn 10% on each sale — it's how we keep the site running without ads.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
